        "content": "*\u201cBy bridging crypto philanthropy with grassroots activism, we\u2019re cultivating a homegrown network that channels Web3 tools straight into the hands of local changemakers\u201d*\n\n### **Founding Story & Key Motivations**\n\nTwo years ago, inspired by the Commons Stack\u2019s Commons Prize, the founders realized Costa Rica\u2019s diverse Web3 communities could achieve more together than apart. By uniting eco-activists, technologists, and rural leaders, they formed ReFi Costa Rica to channel regenerative finance into the country\u2019s social and ecological fabric.\n\n### **What Makes ReFi Costa Rica Special**\n\nReFi Costa Rica merges digital innovation with deep ecological wisdom. In a nation celebrated for environmental stewardship, this node translates ReFi ideals into practical, community-driven models\u2014fostering everything from bioregional financing to educational exchanges.\n\n![Qmb6uvRCKC7ZXEaVhj5zJpJzwNxca7WFAd9yQRwk55ZRfS.jpeg](nodes/refi-costa-rica/images/cover.jpeg)\n\n## 2024 Highlights\n\n### Monthly Crypto Cantinas\n\n1. **What Happened:** Held casual gatherings to help locals set up wallets, learn about NFTs, and explore ReFi tools.\n2. **Why It Matters:** Lowered the barriers to entry, democratising access to Web3 and nurturing a grassroots community ready to apply regenerative principles.\n\n### Full-Day Workshops & Showcases\n\n1. **What Happened:** Brought various Web3 projects together for discussions, presentations, and resource-sharing.\n2. **Why It Matters**: Sparked new collaborations and aligned diverse efforts toward common regenerative goals.\n\n### Research Partnership with National University\n\n1. **What Happened:** Studied how crypto fundraising impacts rural livelihoods, providing data-driven insights.\n2. **Why It Matters:** Offered evidence-based guidance to refine future strategies and ensure Web3 tools truly benefit local communities.\n\n### Bioregional Financing Exploration\n\n1. **What Happened:** Developed concepts for local tokens and community currencies tied to ecosystem restoration.\n2. **Why It Matters:** Set the stage for financial models that reward good stewardship, channelling capital where it amplifies ecological and social gains.\n\n## Vision for 2025\n\n### Leadership Transition & Formalization\n\n1. **What\u2019s Coming:** Current leaders move into advisory roles as fresh, locally-rooted stewards take charge.\n2. **Why It Matters:** Ensures long-term sustainability, local ownership, and a leadership pipeline shaped by community needs.\n\n### Youth Mentorship Programs\n\n1. **What\u2019s Coming:** Training sessions to equip young people with Web3 skills, governance know-how, and ReFi principles.\n2. **Why It Matters:** Cultivates a new generation of ReFi champions who can lead projects that blend technology and tradition.\n\n### TicoBlockchain 2025 Event\n\n1. **What\u2019s Coming:** A flagship gathering uniting stakeholders to share lessons, launch initiatives, and shape future directions.\n2. **Why It Matters:** Positions Costa Rica as a global ReFi hub and crystallises the network\u2019s ambitions into actionable plans.\n\n### Implementing Bioregional Financing Systems\n\n1. **What\u2019s Coming:** Piloting local tokens and frameworks that tie economic growth directly to ecological health.\n2. **Why It Matters:** Moves from theory to action, ensuring that regenerative finance isn\u2019t just an idea but a practical tool for improving livelihoods and landscapes.\n\n![GWrRhQiWgAAThJK.jpeg](nodes/refi-costa-rica/images/refi-costa-rica1.jpeg)\n\n![GWrRjfDX0AApmQO.jpeg](nodes/refi-costa-rica/images/refi-costa-rica3.jpeg)\n\n![GWrRhSpXsAAiNIL.jpeg](nodes/refi-costa-rica/images/refi-costa-rica2.jpeg)",
        "xPct": 23.3,
        "yPct": 64.1,
