        "content": "# **ReFi Hong Kong**\n\n\n**Key Details**\n\n- **Location**: Hong Kong \ud83c\udded\ud83c\uddf0\n- **Node Stage**: Established\n- **Core Contributors:**\u00a0[**Leo Lin**](https://twitter.com/linyao01),\u00a0[**GreaPapa**](https://twitter.com/GreaPapa),\u00a0[**Max Song**](https://twitter.com/Pericarus)\n- **Key Links:**\u00a0[**Twitter: @ReFiHongKong**](https://twitter.com/ReFiHongKong),\u00a0[**Telegram**](https://t.me/+VSCplRPtFwIxYmFk)\n\n**2023 Highlights**\n\n- **Diverse Events:**\u00a0Organized three significant events, including two offline and one online event, to promote Web3 technology and its role in regenerative economics. This includes the inaugural ReFi Hong Kong kick-off event in April alongside the Web3 Festival, co-organized with\u00a0[**Arkreen**](https://arkreen.com/),\u00a0[**Wanxiang Blockchain**](https://twitter.com/WXblockchain),\u00a0[**HashKey Group**](https://group.hashkey.com/en/), and ReFi DAO.\n- **Online Engagement:**\u00a0Conducted the first online Twitter Space in July, featuring discussions with\u00a0[**Carbon World**](https://carboncoins.com.hk/),\u00a0[**RGRT**](http://continuousregeneration.com/),\u00a0[**New Energy Nexus**](https://www.newenergynexus.com/), and\u00a0[**Allinfra**](https://allinfra.com/)\u00a0on ESG and ReFi practices in Hong Kong.\n- **AI+ESG Focus:**\u00a0Partnered with\u00a0[**Carbonbase**](https://www.carbonbase.co/)\u00a0for an offline event in August, focusing on AI and ESG, featuring Patricia from UN Migration, analyzing ESG reports of HKEX-listed companies.\n- **GreenBTC Club Launch:**\u00a0ReFi Hong Kong key partner, Arkreen Network, launched the GreenBTC Club application in November, aiming to build a sustainable Bitcoin Ecosystem and recognizing contributions with Soulbound Tokens.\n\n**2024 Vision & Plans**\n\n- **Expanding GreenBTC:**\u00a0Planning to co-host GreenBTC with other local node communities, leveraging ReFi DAO\u2019s global network to grow the Green Bitcoin Ecosystem.\n- **Community Growth:**\u00a0Focusing on hosting more offline/online events related to ESG, ReFi, and Web3 and expanding the community to 100+ members.\n\n> \u201cMy wish is to witness blockchain and decentralized technologies thriving in harmony with ecological responsibility. I aspire to see our initiatives fostering a sustainable and energy-efficient bitcoin and Web3 ecosystem, where decentralized applications and platforms prioritize environmental consciousness. May this year mark a significant step towards a greener and more sustainable future for the bitcoin and Web3 ecosystem, ensuring that innovation goes hand in hand with ecological responsibility.\u201d -\u00a0Leo Lin\n\n![refihongkong1.jpg](nodes/refi-hong-kong/images/refihongkong1.jpg)\n![refihongkong2.jpg](nodes/refi-hong-kong/images/refihongkong2.jpg)\n![refihongkong3.jpg](nodes/refi-hong-kong/images/refihongkong3.jpg)",
