        "content": "# **ReFi London**\n\n\n**Key Details**\n\n- **Location**: UK \ud83c\uddec\ud83c\udde7\n- **Node Stage**: Incubation\n- **Core Contributors**:\u00a0[**Monty Merlin Bryant**](https://www.linkedin.com/in/montybryant/),\u00a0[**Raam Chandrasekharan**](https://www.linkedin.com/in/raamchandrasekharan/),\u00a0[**Priyank Bakshi**](https://www.linkedin.com/in/priyankbakshi/)\n- **Key Links:**\u00a0[**Linktree**](https://linktr.ee/refilondon),\u00a0[**Twitter: @ReFiLondon**](https://twitter.com/ReFiLondon),\u00a0[**LinkedIn**](https://www.linkedin.com/company/refi-london),\u00a0[**ReFi UK Telegram**](https://t.me/+Acf4NtpO2yIzMzJh),\u00a0[**WhatsApp**](https://chat.whatsapp.com/Fu0hmxBys8BGuikex73hKR)\n\n**2023\u00a0Highlights**\n\n- **Event Sponsorship:**\u00a0Sponsored\u00a0[**Regens Unite London**](https://www.regensunite.earth/event/regens-unite-london)\u2019s first event that saw 50+ attendees and 15+ workshop sessions, including \u2018The Ecosystem: Collaborating towards a new economic system\u2019 by\u00a0[**Rachel Kan**](https://www.linkedin.com/in/rachel-sheila-kan/), \u2018From Network States to Regen CoordiNATION\u2019 by\u00a0[**Monty Merlin**](https://www.linkedin.com/in/montybryant/), and \u2018The Wellbeing Protocol - Building Community Wellbeing DAOs\u2019 by\u00a0[**Mark Pascall**](https://www.linkedin.com/in/markpascall/).\n- **Established Connections:**\u00a0Partnered with the GreenPill UK chapter and Regens Unite London.\n\n**2024\u00a0Vision & Plans**\n\n- **ReFi London Events**: Kicking things off with a meetup during the upcoming\u00a0[**ETH London**](https://ethglobal.com/events/london2024), they aim to lead combined ReFi London x GreenPill UK x Regens Unite events and meetups. Furthermore, recognizing London's unparalleled position as a hub of talent and innovation, in addition to core ReFi & Web3 community members, they aim to attract public, private, and third-sector leaders.\n- **ReFi London Knowledge Graph & Website**: Fuelling the further development of the ReFi London Knowledge Graph and its website. This platform will serve as a comprehensive map of London's regenerative economy ecosystem and locally aligned projects.\n\n> \u201cThe roots of ReFi London are embedded in the global ambition of ReFi DAO\u2014a vision to cultivate a worldwide regenerative economy through a network of interconnected local communities. ReFi London aspires to be a beacon among these Nodes, rallying high-impact leaders; contributing to ReFi DAO; and leveraging London's leadership in finance, entrepreneurship, technology, and academia for positive change.\u201d -\u00a0Monty Merlin Bryant",
